node.text:
As many parts of the country re-open, many of us are returning to a version of the family vacations, backyard BBQs, and holiday celebrations we had to cancel last year. 

After all those video calls and socially distanced visits, we've realized that we are simply better together when we can celebrate life in person. 

This Father's Day, show the dads in your life how much you care by giving them germ-killing power with PhoneSoap. Our UV disinfection tools are the gifts they'll love—and use—to stay healthy.

node.text:
Smoke belongs in your grill (@traegergrills) not in your home. 

Keep your air fresh and free from smoke and other unhealthy air pollutants with AirSoap.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"If you take your phone with you absolutely everywhere you go, it's probably time to add a PhoneSoap to your daily routine." TODAY'.

node.text: When you really think about it, where has your phone NOT been? And when was the last time it was cleaned or sanitized? Yuck, right? PhoneSoap can help make sure your phone doesn't get you sick.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 29, 2021. May be an image of furniture and indoor.

node.text: We care about our air and our planet. Luckily, AirSoap helps with both. AirSoap kills 99.99% of airborne viruses and uses washable, reusable collection plates instead of costly and wasteful HEPA filters.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 28, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Why You Shouldn't Use Alcohol to Clean Your Phone'.

node.text:
👏🏻 Stop using alcohol to clean your phone!👏🏻 Here's why ☝🏻

We've got a better way to disinfect your phone: PhoneSoap uses no heat or chemicals to sanitize your phone, removing 99.99% of harmful bacteria and germs. Our 360-degree disinfection means no corner or edge is missed.

node.text: When do you sanitize your phone? In the morning after a gym session? While you brush your teeth at night? Or while you're cooking up a quick meal? The possibilities are endless when it only takes 10 minutes to reduce 99.99% of bacteria and viruses lingering on your screen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 20, 2021. May be an image of phone.

node.text: More bulbs, more space, more sanitizing power, and more charging capabilities. Who doesn't want MORE?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text: TikTok can wait for 5 minutes. Your phone is gross, so throw it in the PhoneSoap Pro while you reheat your leftovers or unload the dishwasher.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"Great for getting rid of all the pollen and dander in the house. My nose could be all clogged up outside, but rapidly clears when / come inside. Also love the fact it's proven to get rid of germs considering the little children that come to visit." -Marie K.'.

node.text: Allergies acting up? Wait! Have you tried the AirSoap? Marie has and now she's got a clear nose and a germ-, pollen-, AND dander-free house. Can't beat that.

Stars, Stripes, and a Smudge-Free Screen. 
Clean that funky phone screen. Our PhoneSoap Shine and PhoneSoap Pads do the trick!

Now go nail a perfect fireworks pic. Happy 4th! 🇺🇸

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by PhoneSoap on July 03, 2021. May be an image of saddle-stitched leather.

node.text: Rihanna was inspired by our PhoneSoap Shines when she wrote the lyrics "shine bright like a diamond." Spray our cleaning solution onto your phone and then use the built-in microfiber cloth to make your screen shine.

Our UV disinfection devices kill 99.99% of germs from off your phone but they can't get rid of smudges and streaks. Enter: PhoneSoap Pads. The microfiber cloth safely cleans any screen and once you're done wiping your phone, you can just toss them in the washing machine!
Charge your device and eliminate germs? Sign us up. Our charging cables come in three lengths and use embedded metallic ions to self-disinfect over 24 hours.
